  "prompt": "How does international law intersect with national laws on money laundering?",
  "response": "International law intersects with national laws on money laundering in several important ways:\n\n1. Global Regulatory Frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) sets international standards\n- UN Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime provides guidelines\n- Basel Committee on Banking Supervision establishes international banking regulations\n\n2. Mutual Legal Assistance\n- Countries cooperate in investigating and prosecuting money laundering cases\n- Extradition treaties facilitate cross-border legal proceedings\n- Information sharing between financial intelligence units\n\n3. Compliance Requirements\n- Banks and financial institutions must implement international anti-money laundering (AML) protocols\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious transaction reporting mechanisms\n\n4. Sanctions and Enforcement\n- International sanctions against countries with weak AML frameworks\n- Coordinated efforts to freeze assets of suspected money launderers\n- Bilateral and multilateral enforcement agreements\n\n5. Legal Harmonization\n- Countries align national legislation with international standards\n- Consistent definitions of money laundering offenses\n- Standardized due diligence procedures\n\n6. Technology and Digital Currencies\n- Emerging international regulations for cryptocurrency transactions\n- Cross-border tracking of digital financial activities\n\nThese intersections create a complex, integrated approach to combating money laundering globally.",
